  { q: 'How much does smart thermostat installation cost in Tampa?', a: 'Installation-only service (you provide the thermostat) is typically $149 to $199. A complete supply-and-install of an Ecobee, Nest, or Honeywell T9 runs $300 to $500 depending on model and any C-wire adapter work needed.' },
  { q: 'What is the best smart thermostat for a Florida home?', a: 'Ecobee Premium and Honeywell T10 lead our list for multi-stage heat pumps, the most common Tampa setup. Google Nest Learning works beautifully for single-stage systems. Every model we install supports humidity control, which is critical in Tampa.' },
  { q: 'My system does not have a C-wire. Can I still upgrade?', a: 'Almost always yes. We install a C-wire adapter (PEK or similar) at the air handler or run a new thermostat cable if the wall cavity allows. About 70% of older Tampa homes we retrofit need some form of C-wire solution.' },
  { q: 'Can a smart thermostat actually save me money?', a: 'Ecobee and Google both publish third-party verified data showing around 23% average cooling savings vs. manual thermostats. Real Tampa homes often see $15 to $40 per month in summer savings once humidity-aware scheduling is dialed in.' },
  { q: 'Will it work with my heat pump and heat strips?', a: 'Yes, but it needs to be wired and configured correctly. A misconfigured smart thermostat will run your heat strips unnecessarily and spike winter bills. We configure the stages, lockouts, and dehumidifier control as part of the install.' },
